import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_obesity_rate = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='rate', data=avg_obesity_rate)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.axhline(avg_obesity_rate['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {avg_obesity_rate['rate'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average obesity rate across all states and dates?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    max_obesity_state = data.loc[data['rate'].idxmax()]['state']
    max_obesity_rate = data['rate'].max()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.axhline(y=max_obesity_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Obesity Rate: {max_obesity_rate:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('Which state has the highest obesity rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
